
Install steps: https://docs.fedoraproject.org/en-US/fedora-coreos/bare-metal/

Install coreos-installer: $ sudo dnf install coreos-installer
Install Butane: $ sudo dnf install -y butane
Create a basic Ignition config that modifies the default Fedora CoreOS user core to allow this user to log in with an SSH key:
  Create the file example.bu with the following contents:
variant: fcos
version: 1.4.0
passwd:
  users:
    - name: core
      ssh_authorized_keys:
        - ssh-rsa AAAA...


  
  Run Butane on the Butane config: $ butane --pretty --strict example.bu > example.ign
Convert the Ignission file to JSON:
Install CoreOS: sudo coreos-installer install /dev/nvme0n1 --ignition-url https://example.com/example.ign
Reboot: $ sudo reboot
